.TH history-prune 1  "history-prune " 
.SH NAME
history\-prune \- Prune or compact run history according to a retention policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBhistory\-prune\fR [\fB\-\-max\-records\fR] [\fB\-\-max\-age\-days\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prune or compact run history according to a retention policy
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-records\fR \fI<N>\fR
Keep only the N most\-recent history records; oldest are removed first.

Takes precedence over `\-\-history\-max\-records` (the global flag) when both are supplied, so you can override the default policy for a single explicit prune operation.
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-age\-days\fR \fI<DAYS>\fR
Remove records older than N days.

Takes precedence over `\-\-history\-max\-age\-days` (the global flag).
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be removed without writing any changes to disk
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
